Quality is terrible, highly pixelated video and audio is far out of sync. I'd rather watch a lower resolution movie that is consistent and in sync than a hi-def one that isn't.

Not only is the quality so bad: audio nearly two seconds out of sync, video pixelated and jumping frames, but less than ten minutes into it, the movie is so bad (movie-wise), that I stopped it and deleted the file.

Don't waste your time.
